  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Logistics Admin. Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Logistics Admin. Executive (Semiconductor Trading Company / 5 days, 9am-6pm / No OT /air-con office environment / Tai Seng)</strong><br /></p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Responsible for the logistics function, including invoicing and <strong>inventory data management</strong>.</li><li>Ensure efficient and smooth running of all logistics daily operations.</li><li>Perform daily data entry duties into operating systems.</li><li>Usage of WMS for inventory system.</li><li>Usage of ERP system to process documents.</li><li>Ensure all shipment documentation are prepared correctly, including document verification throughout the whole process.</li><li>Arrange and liaise with freight forwarders on import & export shipments, including shipment bookings, schedules and all documentation with document verification.</li><li>Preparation of daily incoming and outgoing stock reports.</li><li>Any other ad-hoc duties assigned</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Candidate must possess at least a Diploma in Logistics / Supply Chain Management or equivalent.</li><li>Meticulous, high level of initiative and attention to detail and a good team player.</li><li>Able to multitask and work under pressure.</li><li>2 – 3 years’ experience in logistics admin. role in the similar industry will be an added advantage.</li><li>Proficiency in Microsoft Excel.</li><li>Good communication and interpersonal skills to maintain relationships with internal and external stakeholders.</li><li>Only Singaporean to apply. No quota.</li><li>Able to start work with short notice.</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Benefits and Others:</strong></p><ul><li>Year-end bonus, medical, birthday voucher, insurance and more</li><li>5 days (9am to 6pm daily)</li><li>Near Tai Seng MRT</li><li>Air-con office environment</li></ul><p><strong>**Only shortlisted candidates would be notified**</strong></p>",
